Busy house in which giant parties were organized was evacuated
The house-owners had filled 11 of the 13 apartments in the building at the street of Balmes no. 51 (Barcelona).
The twelve squatters left the building yesterday afternoon without having achieved resistance.
Everything refers to the nightmares of the neighbors of the house no. 51 thinking an end of the street Balmes.
Twelve persons left yesterday noon the building voluntarily, who fills it illegally held and in that they had organized gigantic celebrations, that had driven the neighborhood for the despair. The clearing occurred on judicial order without without police intervention.
After the clearing the door lock was exchanged in order to avoid a similar situation.
"From now on the admission will be controlled", confirmed the house supervisor.
The squatters who had filled 11 of the 13 apartments of the building - the remaining ones were inhabited - took along the entire electric installation and part of the water supply. In addition they had painted the walls and all kinds of garbage leave behind, particularly cans with alcoholic drinks.
In the three lower floors gigantic Partys were celebrated which lasted up to two days and drove the tenants for the despair.
There is a disco, Balmes 51 which took also damages from that, next to the building.
Your holder, Maria Pantinat declared Europe Press that their business would have fallen off about 80% since beginning of the house occupation.
The owner of the disco referred to the squatters doing her unfair competition, because they sold the drinks to three euros while these were costing 10 euros in the disco.
In addition the owner of the leisure time restaurant had been announced by the neighbors because of disturbance, during aloud their statement the noise not of the visitors the disco came, but of the squatters and in particular of the guests of the celebrations that were organized there, and that became according to statements of the annoyed neighbors in the last weeks more and more and longer.
The person responsible of the disco declared that the molestation was so great that they came with the owner of the building ueberein, not to have to pay any rent for the last nine months.
Also the Guardia Urbana (urban police) also confirmed that she received more complaints of the neighbors in the last weeks.
The chairperson the PP (Partido Popular - people's party) in the town council of Barcelona, Alberto Fernández Díaz, last week had demanded, to evacuate the building immediately and to get the problems of the middle class coexistence as well as the coming down of the quarter into the grip.
It declared that before the summer only a floor of the building was busy, but that the squatters had advanced into all floors of the building and almost all apartments in the last months. Into some it had resulted even in thefts.
In this sense he added that it is necessary to put an end to the impunity and to act against the unsocial actions in the building."
